    "content": "\n# Getting Started for Merchants\n\nThis guide will help you migrate your WooCommerce store to BigCommerce using the BC Migration tool.\n\n## What You'll Need\n\nBefore starting your migration, make sure you have:\n\n- **WooCommerce Store**: Admin access to your WooCommerce store\n- **WooCommerce API Keys**: Consumer Key and Secret from WooCommerce → Settings → Advanced → REST API\n- **BigCommerce Store**: An active BigCommerce store (trial or paid)\n- **BigCommerce API Credentials**: Store Hash and Access Token from BigCommerce → Settings → API → Store-level API accounts\n- **Time**: Plan for 2-4 hours for a small store (under 1,000 products)\n\n## Migration Overview\n\nThe migration happens in four phases:\n\n### Phase 1: Foundation\nConnect your stores and run an assessment to understand what will be migrated.\n\n### Phase 2: Core Data\nMigrate categories, products, and their attributes. This is typically the longest phase.\n\n### Phase 3: Transactions\nMigrate customer data, orders, and coupon codes.\n\n### Phase 4: Content\nMigrate blog posts, pages, and product reviews.\n\n## Step-by-Step Process\n\n### 1. Connect Your WooCommerce Store\n\n1. Navigate to the **Dashboard**\n2. Click **Configure WooCommerce Connection**\n3. Enter your store information:\n   - **Store URL**: Your WooCommerce site (e.g., `https://mystore.com`)\n   - **Consumer Key**: From WooCommerce REST API settings\n   - **Consumer Secret**: From WooCommerce REST API settings\n4. Click **Save Connection**\n\nThe system will test the connection automatically.\n\n### 2. Connect Your BigCommerce Store\n\n1. Click **Configure BigCommerce Connection**\n2. Enter your store credentials:\n   - **Store Hash**: Found in your BigCommerce API settings (format: `abc123xyz`)\n   - **Access Token**: Generated from BigCommerce store-level API accounts\n   - **Client ID**: From your API account (optional for migration, required for BC Bridge)\n3. Click **Save Connection**\n\n### 3. Run Assessment\n\nBefore migrating, run an assessment to see what can be transferred:\n\n1. Click **Run Assessment**\n2. Wait 2-5 minutes while the tool scans your WooCommerce store\n3. Review the assessment report:\n   - **Products**: How many products and variants\n   - **Categories**: Category structure and depth\n   - **Customers**: Customer accounts and order history\n   - **Orders**: Total orders and statuses\n   - **Issues**: Any potential problems detected\n\nThe assessment helps identify issues before migration starts.\n\n### 4. Start Migration\n\nOnce you're ready:\n\n1. Navigate to the **Migration Wizard**\n2. The wizard will guide you through all four phases\n3. Each phase shows:\n   - **What will be migrated**\n   - **Estimated time**\n   - **Progress indicator**\n4. Click **Start Phase** for each section\n\n**Important**: You can pause and resume migration at any time. Progress is saved automatically.\n\n### 5. Monitor Progress\n\nWatch the real-time progress bars for:\n- Categories being created\n- Products being migrated\n- Customers being transferred\n- Orders being imported\n\nIf errors occur, they're logged and you can retry failed items.\n\n### 6. Verify Migration\n\nAfter each phase completes:\n\n1. **Check BigCommerce**: Log in to your BigCommerce admin\n2. **Verify Data**:\n   - Products have correct prices and images\n   - Categories are properly nested\n   - Customer accounts are accessible\n3. **Test Checkout**: Place a test order to ensure everything works\n4. **Review Redirects**: Export URL redirects to avoid broken links\n\n## What Gets Migrated\n\n### ✅ Migrated Automatically\n\n- **Products**: Titles, descriptions, SKUs, prices, images, variants\n- **Categories**: Names, descriptions, hierarchies, images\n- **Customers**: Names, emails, addresses (passwords reset required)\n- **Orders**: Order history, statuses, line items, totals\n- **Coupons**: Discount codes and rules (where compatible)\n- **Reviews**: Product reviews and ratings\n- **Pages**: WordPress pages as BigCommerce web pages\n- **Blog**: WordPress posts to BigCommerce blog\n\n### ⚠️ Requires Manual Setup\n\n- **Theme/Design**: BigCommerce uses different themes (consider Catalyst or Stencil)\n- **Custom Fields**: WooCommerce custom fields need manual mapping\n- **Plugins**: WooCommerce plugins don't transfer (find BigCommerce alternatives)\n- **Payment Gateways**: Reconfigure in BigCommerce settings\n- **Shipping**: Set up shipping zones and rates in BigCommerce\n\n### ❌ Not Migrated\n\n- **User passwords**: Customers need to reset passwords\n- **Plugin data**: Third-party plugin data structures\n- **Draft products**: Only published products migrate\n- **Internal notes**: Private order notes don't transfer\n\n## After Migration\n\n### 1. Post-Migration Checklist\n\n- [ ] Test all product pages for correct pricing and images\n- [ ] Verify category navigation works\n- [ ] Check customer accounts can log in (after password reset)\n- [ ] Test checkout process end-to-end\n- [ ] Configure shipping zones and rates\n- [ ] Set up payment gateways\n- [ ] Configure tax settings\n- [ ] Set up email notifications\n- [ ] Test on mobile devices\n\n### 2. URL Redirects\n\nExport and implement redirects to maintain SEO:\n\n1. Download the redirect CSV from **Assessment → Export Redirects**\n2. Implement in:\n   - **BigCommerce**: Settings → Redirects (manually)\n   - **CDN**: Cloudflare/Fastly rules (bulk)\n   - **Server**: nginx/Apache rules (via .htaccess)\n\n### 3. Go Live\n\nWhen ready to switch:\n\n1. **Backup**: Create full backup of WooCommerce store\n2. **Final Migration**: Run migration one last time to capture recent orders\n3. **DNS**: Update DNS to point to BigCommerce\n4. **Monitor**: Watch for errors in first 24-48 hours\n5. **Support**: Have support resources ready for customer questions\n\n## Common Issues\n\n### \"Connection Failed\"\n- **WooCommerce**: Check API keys have read/write permissions\n- **BigCommerce**: Verify Access Token hasn't expired\n- **Network**: Ensure firewall allows API connections\n\n### \"Product Import Failed\"\n- **SKU Conflicts**: BigCommerce requires unique SKUs\n- **Invalid Prices**: Check for non-numeric price values\n- **Missing Images**: Verify image URLs are accessible\n\n### \"Customer Import Skipped\"\n- **Duplicate Emails**: BigCommerce requires unique customer emails\n- **Invalid Data**: Check for malformed email addresses\n\n## Getting Help\n\n- **Dashboard**: Check the built-in help panel (? icon)\n- **Troubleshooting**: See [Troubleshooting Guide](/docs/troubleshooting/common-issues)\n- **Support**: Contact your agency or migration partner\n- **Community**: BigCommerce community forums\n\n## Next Steps\n\n- [WooCommerce to BigCommerce Differences](/docs/guides/platform-differences)\n- [Setting Up BC Bridge Plugin](/docs/guides/bc-bridge/installation)\n- [Optimizing Your BigCommerce Store](/docs/guides/post-migration/optimization)\n",
